Name: sgTicksPerGameTurn?
What?: Array of 7 longs, from slowest to fastest game speed, containing the milliseconds spent in each frame

Name: g_ActiveNationID
What?: Active player ID (same as local nation id in trigger context)
gwRacePort_g, portrait ID for each race's advisor

Name: sgnPercent
What?: Weapon type multipliers, against each unit size type
latencyFrameCount, long for each game speed
fowUpdateCounter, delay counter for updating the fog of war (set to 1 to update instantely)

Name: sgpImgGroups_g
What?: Pointers to the graphics for each image type

Name: sgImages
What?: image array access (individual images in the game)

Name: gPlayerData
What?: Player information structures (name, race, force, etc)
pGameScreenInfo, Some console mask related thing
minimap palette, Some kind of minimap palette (256 bytes)

Name: sgbNextMsg
What?: nextDisplayTextLine, The line that the next text message will display on

Name: sgwTriggerUpdateTimer_g
What?: triggerTimer, number of frames between trigger checks

Name: sgdwTriggerPlayer
What?: currentTrigPlayerID, Current player ID for triggers

Name: sgbBitMask
What?: Fog of war mask for revealed areas

Name: g_find_arr_flag
What?: unitFinderFlags, Array of per-unit flags indicating whether a particular unit index is found by the unit finder (set by region checking functions).
sgbPens_g, palette index for pen colours
